.TH CHMOD 1 "2026-05-18" "OurOS" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
chmod \- change file mode bits
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B chmod
[\fIOPTIONS\fR] \fIMODE\fR \fIFILE\fR...
.SH DESCRIPTION
Change the mode (permissions) of each FILE to MODE.  MODE can be
specified symbolically (u+x, go-w) or as an octal number (755).
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-R\fR, \fB\-\-recursive\fR
Change files and directories recursively.
.TP
\fB\-v\fR, \fB\-\-verbose\fR
Output a diagnostic for every file processed.
.TP
\fB\-c\fR, \fB\-\-changes\fR
Like verbose but report only when a change is made.
.TP
\fB\-f\fR, \fB\-\-silent\fR, \fB\-\-quiet\fR
Suppress most error messages.
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
chmod 755 script.sh         Make executable by all
chmod u+x program           Add execute for owner
chmod -R go-w project/      Remove group/other write recursively
chmod a=r readonly.txt      Read-only for everyone
.fi
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR chown (1),
.BR ls (1),
.BR stat (1)
.SH AUTHOR
OurOS Contributors.
